y apply to that specific instance and reset when calling `AppDbConnection#prepareStatement` again.\n\nI'm noticing the knowledge file structure has the \"иЁӯе®ҡеҶ…е®№и©ізҙ°\" section mixing both the XML configuration example and property descriptions together. Now I'm verifying the knowledge file against the source documentation. The BasicSqlLoader extension defaults to \"sql\" which matches what the source specifies, and the fetchSize default of 10 is also correct. I'm checking queryTimeout next to confirm it's accurately captured.\n\nLooking at the source XML structure...\n\nI'm noticing the knowledge file correctly captured the StatementFactory configuration with properties like fetchSize set to 500 and queryTimeout at 600 seconds. The source has a malformed comment tag (`<!==` instead of `<!--`), but the knowledge file properly uses standard XML comment syntax, which is actually an improvement. The SqlLoader component configuration with UTF-8 encoding and .sql file extension matches what's documented. I'm noticing the RST heading hierarchy doesn't quite match up with how the knowledge file organized things. The source has \"иЁӯе®ҡгғ•гӮЎгӮӨгғ«дҫӢ\" as a top-level section with equal signs, but \"JavaгҒ®е®ҹиЈ…дҫӢ\" as a subsection with dashes above it. The knowledge file seems to have flattened this structure, treating \"иЁӯе®ҡгғ•гӮЎгӮӨгғ«дҫӢ\" as the main title and grouping the detailed settings under it as s2.\n\nNow I'm checking the hints against what's actually in each section - s1 covers the Java implementation details with classes like AppDbConnection and SqlPStatement, while s2 includes the configuration file content and the factory classes like BasicStatementFactory and BasicSqlLoader. I'm noticing the `Map<String, String>` type hint is missing from the s2 hints, though that's probably fine. Let me do a more thorough check for any other gaps or inaccuracies I might have missed, and I'm reviewing the fetchSize behavior documentation to make sure I understand